Sauron News
============

Version 0.1.4 (Development)
---------------------------
Build system:
- Consolidated version to single source of truth in m4/version.m4
- Version components (MAJOR, MINOR, PATCH) now generated in config.h
- Added configure check for getopt_long availability
- Fixed distcheck issues with missing/incorrect file references
- Removed CLAUDE.md from distribution tarball

CLI improvements:
- Long options (--help, --version, --debug, --file) when getopt_long available
- Graceful fallback to short options on systems without getopt_long
- Help text adapts to show available option formats

Version 0.1.1
---------------------------
New features:
- Bulk loading from CSV files (sauron_bulk_load, sauron_bulk_load_buffer)
- Extended get with explicit not-found handling (sauron_get_ex)
- Clear all scores without destroy/create (sauron_clear)
- Iteration over all scored IPs (sauron_foreach)
- Batch increment operation (sauron_incr_batch)
- Safe IP formatting function (sauron_u32_to_ip_s)

Testing:
- Added comprehensive edge case tests (88 new tests)
- Added concurrent stress test examples
- Total test count: 135 tests across 4 test files

Documentation:
- Complete C and Python API reference in README.md
- Updated man pages with new functions
- Updated architecture documentation

Version 0.1.0 (2026-01-16)
---------------------------
- Initial release
- Core scoring engine with /24 CIDR blocks
- Two-level lookup with 2MB bitmap filter
- Lock-free reads, per-block spinlock writes
- Decay operation with deadzone
- Binary archive persistence (atomic save/load)
- CLI utility for testing
- Python bindings (ctypes)
- Performance: 165M reads/sec, 39M writes/sec (single-threaded)
